00:26:04.210 --> 00:26:10.860 align:middle line:84%
And he recognized me on
a very nonverbal level.

00:26:10.860 --> 00:26:15.380 align:middle line:84%
And I must add here that
my connections with animals

00:26:15.380 --> 00:26:16.680 align:middle line:90%
never required words.

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:19.590 align:middle line:90%


00:26:19.590 --> 00:26:21.800 align:middle line:84%
The entire time
I was growing up,

00:26:21.800 --> 00:26:24.770 align:middle line:84%
through all of my work,
my veterinary work,

00:26:24.770 --> 00:26:29.880 align:middle line:84%
rarely did I ever
need to assign words.

00:26:29.880 --> 00:26:33.270 align:middle line:84%
That only came later, when I had
an encounter, also in Africa,

00:26:33.270 --> 00:26:34.060 align:middle line:90%
with some buffalo.

00:26:34.060 --> 00:26:34.970 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:26:34.970 --> 00:26:40.810 align:middle line:84%
But I did receive amazing
insight about elephants

00:26:40.810 --> 00:26:45.110 align:middle line:84%
and their capacity
to share wisdom,

00:26:45.110 --> 00:26:47.522 align:middle line:84%
because elephants really
are the symbol of wisdom.

00:26:47.522 --> 00:26:48.755 align:middle line:84%
REGINA MEREDITH:
Wisdom keepers, yes.

00:26:48.755 --> 00:26:50.550 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: The
wisdom keepers,

00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:52.240 align:middle line:90%
and the ancient traditions.

00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:59.460 align:middle line:84%
And they are-- what these
elephants really explained

00:26:59.460 --> 00:27:04.470 align:middle line:84%
to me nonverbally was
how integrated they are,

00:27:04.470 --> 00:27:07.980 align:middle line:84%
and how connected they are
to the other animal cultures

00:27:07.980 --> 00:27:10.730 align:middle line:84%
that they live and
share the land with.

00:27:10.730 --> 00:27:16.150 align:middle line:84%
And they shared other tidbits
about some of those cultures.

00:27:16.150 --> 00:27:19.530 align:middle line:84%
For example, be careful
to love the birds.

00:27:19.530 --> 00:27:23.620 align:middle line:84%
And then they would talk about
what they loved about birds.

00:27:23.620 --> 00:27:27.240 align:middle line:84%
How the lions loved the birds
and the songs of the birds.

00:27:27.240 --> 00:27:30.185 align:middle line:84%
How we must be mindful of the
giraffe, because the giraffe

00:27:30.185 --> 00:27:31.920 align:middle line:90%
are the tall beings.

00:27:31.920 --> 00:27:37.580 align:middle line:84%
And they watch out and scan
for other predator animals.

00:27:37.580 --> 00:27:41.430 align:middle line:84%
How the giraffe also
connect to the elephants.

00:27:41.430 --> 00:27:44.820 align:middle line:84%
And the elephants
are the matriarchs,

00:27:44.820 --> 00:27:47.940 align:middle line:84%
and the females are always
careful to protect their young.

00:27:47.940 --> 00:27:50.400 align:middle line:84%
Their young stick with the
mother for a good four--

00:27:50.400 --> 00:27:51.300 align:middle line:90%
They're very good mothers.

00:27:51.300 --> 00:27:53.470 align:middle line:84%
---over four years, they
nurse, which is part

00:27:53.470 --> 00:27:55.040 align:middle line:90%
of the problem with poaching.

00:27:55.040 --> 00:27:59.200 align:middle line:84%
If a mom is poached, the infant
will also die unless it's

00:27:59.200 --> 00:28:02.200 align:middle line:90%
over the age of nursing.

00:28:02.200 --> 00:28:07.080 align:middle line:84%
So they shared these
loving sacred stories

00:28:07.080 --> 00:28:09.790 align:middle line:84%
of the connections of these
different animal cultures

00:28:09.790 --> 00:28:10.915 align:middle line:90%
to me.

00:28:10.915 --> 00:28:12.100 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:28:12.100 --> 00:28:14.170 align:middle line:84%
What a privilege for you.
LINDA BENDER: It was.

00:28:14.170 --> 00:28:14.880 align:middle line:90%
It still is.

00:28:14.880 --> 00:28:15.780 align:middle line:90%
And thank you for sharing.

00:28:15.780 --> 00:28:16.590 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:28:16.590 --> 00:28:18.455 align:middle line:84%
And thank you for
sharing that with us.

00:28:18.455 --> 00:28:19.255 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Thank you.

00:28:19.255 --> 00:28:20.521 align:middle line:84%
REGINA MEREDITH: I
mean, I'm with you,

