00:30:12.660 --> 00:30:16.500 align:middle line:84%
And I think that was the
point where we actually

00:30:16.500 --> 00:30:19.940 align:middle line:84%
couldn't bear it any longer, and
actually called out his name.

00:30:19.940 --> 00:30:25.520 align:middle line:90%


00:30:25.520 --> 00:30:28.720 align:middle line:84%
And at that moment,
the pace picks up.

00:30:28.720 --> 00:30:32.206 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30:32.206 --> 00:30:51.628 align:middle line:90%


00:30:51.628 --> 00:30:53.372 align:middle line:84%
MALE SPEAKER 2:
And he was just so,

00:30:53.372 --> 00:30:56.580 align:middle line:84%
so excited, because we were.
[INAUDIBLE]

00:30:56.580 --> 00:31:03.885 align:middle line:90%


00:31:03.885 --> 00:31:07.510 align:middle line:84%
MALE SPEAKER 1 : It it's
just an incredible reunion.

00:31:07.510 --> 00:31:10.960 align:middle line:84%
Whether we were human or he was
animal was totally irrelevant.

00:31:10.960 --> 00:31:17.373 align:middle line:90%


00:31:17.373 --> 00:31:19.728 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:19.728 --> 00:31:20.930 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god.

00:31:20.930 --> 00:31:24.610 align:middle line:84%
To me, that is one of the
most joyful films ever.

00:31:24.610 --> 00:31:25.950 align:middle line:84%
It still brings
tears to my eyes--

00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:26.650 align:middle line:90%
Oh my gosh, me too.

00:31:26.650 --> 00:31:28.660 align:middle line:84%
--[INAUDIBLE] times
since I've seen it.

00:31:28.660 --> 00:31:31.311 align:middle line:84%
And I just have to
say, I rest my case.

00:31:31.311 --> 00:31:32.010 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:31:32.010 --> 00:31:38.341 align:middle line:84%
Anyone who doubts the emotional
and loving capacity of animals.

00:31:38.341 --> 00:31:39.040 align:middle line:90%
Of animals.

00:31:39.040 --> 00:31:41.331 align:middle line:84%
After everything we have done
to them and their environment--

00:31:41.331 --> 00:31:42.030 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:31:42.030 --> 00:31:45.361 align:middle line:84%
---to still show up with a
completely open heart for us.

00:31:45.361 --> 00:31:47.140 align:middle line:84%
-Yes.
-Well, OK.

00:31:47.140 --> 00:31:47.840 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:31:47.840 --> 00:31:51.400 align:middle line:84%
That is-- and you have a
personal lion story too.

00:31:51.400 --> 00:31:55.840 align:middle line:10%
Well, I have many lion stories,
but there's one I would like

00:31:55.840 --> 00:32:01.570 align:middle line:10%
to share, because as we just
witnessed, the great love--

00:32:01.570 --> 00:32:08.230 align:middle line:10%
and I'm getting a little
[INAUDIBLE] worked

00:32:08.230 --> 00:32:10.040 align:middle line:10%
up over that precious moment--

00:32:10.040 --> 00:32:10.740 align:middle line:10%
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:32:10.740 --> 00:32:13.410 align:middle line:90%
---as I think we all should.

00:32:13.410 --> 00:32:17.960 align:middle line:84%
But we do identify
lions with courage.

00:32:17.960 --> 00:32:23.060 align:middle line:84%
We identify lions with heart,
with so many of those words

00:32:23.060 --> 00:32:26.000 align:middle line:90%
to have become over used.

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:32.250 align:middle line:84%
But I would invite you
to take it a step deeper

00:32:32.250 --> 00:32:39.570 align:middle line:84%
and allow lions to share a more
sacred meaning of what it means

00:32:39.570 --> 00:32:42.480 align:middle line:84%
to be courageous, what
it means to be loving,

00:32:42.480 --> 00:32:46.280 align:middle line:84%
and what it means
to be prideful.

00:32:46.280 --> 00:32:49.760 align:middle line:84%
And from the level of
the heart and the soul,

00:32:49.760 --> 00:32:52.900 align:middle line:84%
what lions teach us
is, as the beings

00:32:52.900 --> 00:32:56.420 align:middle line:84%
who are the top of the
mountain, the ones who watch

00:32:56.420 --> 00:33:00.160 align:middle line:84%
over all beings
in their kingdom,

00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:02.515 align:middle line:84%
they are the great
beings of courage.

00:33:02.515 --> 00:33:06.160 align:middle line:84%
And courage to me, through my
life with working with animals,

00:33:06.160 --> 00:33:10.070 align:middle line:84%
has always been courage is
not getting rid of fear.

00:33:10.070 --> 00:33:13.980 align:middle line:84%
Courage, as lions know courage,
is courage to look fear

00:33:13.980 --> 00:33:15.150 align:middle line:90%
in the face.

00:33:15.150 --> 00:33:16.546 align:middle line:90%
And who is this?

00:33:16.546 --> 00:33:24.750 align:middle line:84%
This is a most magnificent
white lion from the Timbavati

00:33:24.750 --> 00:33:26.990 align:middle line:90%
area of South Africa.

00:33:26.990 --> 00:33:31.940 align:middle line:84%
This particular
lion in this photo

00:33:31.940 --> 00:33:38.200 align:middle line:84%
is demonstrating the
majestic lion quality.

00:33:38.200 --> 00:33:44.480 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to tell you that this
beautiful lion had this photo

00:33:44.480 --> 00:33:51.090 align:middle line:84%
taken as he was released
from a hunting camp,

00:33:51.090 --> 00:33:54.170 align:middle line:90%
where he spent his entire life.

00:33:54.170 --> 00:33:58.421 align:middle line:84%
He had never been out
of a dark caged area.

00:33:58.421 --> 00:33:59.120 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:33:59.120 --> 00:34:04.790 align:middle line:84%
He was raised to be part
of the hunting trade.

00:34:04.790 --> 00:34:08.230 align:middle line:84%
And this photo was
taken when he was

00:34:08.230 --> 00:34:13.340 align:middle line:84%
rescued, and stepped
onto real ground

00:34:13.340 --> 00:34:14.929 align:middle line:90%
for the first time in his life.

00:34:14.929 --> 00:34:17.054 align:middle line:90%
And he was 11 years old.

00:34:17.054 --> 00:34:19.489 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Oh my god.

00:34:19.489 --> 00:34:24.960 align:middle line:84%
That-- that's-- look
at his eyes, his face.

00:34:24.960 --> 00:34:26.797 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: This is
the face of courage.

00:34:26.797 --> 00:34:27.730 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Oh my gosh.

00:34:27.730 --> 00:34:30.960 align:middle line:84%
It's just so powerful,
overwhelmingly powerful.

00:34:30.960 --> 00:34:33.030 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for
sharing that story.

00:34:33.030 --> 00:34:36.050 align:middle line:84%
And there are a lot
of others like him

00:34:36.050 --> 00:34:37.671 align:middle line:84%
that are living that
same kind of existence.

00:34:37.671 --> 00:34:38.370 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:34:38.370 --> 00:34:40.130 align:middle line:84%
Not allowed to roam
their own land anymore.

00:34:40.130 --> 00:34:42.850 align:middle line:84%
And this is the only
place in the world

00:34:42.850 --> 00:34:47.080 align:middle line:84%
that these sacred lions
have ever, ever lived.

00:34:47.080 --> 00:34:49.730 align:middle line:84%
And the shamans, the
indigenous people,

00:34:49.730 --> 00:34:54.570 align:middle line:84%
have wonderful sacred stories
about them as the star beings--

00:34:54.570 --> 00:35:00.030 align:middle line:84%
and have many, many, many sacred
stories about those beings.

00:35:00.030 --> 00:35:03.100 align:middle line:84%
As connected to other star
systems that have come here--

00:35:03.100 --> 00:35:03.900 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Come here.

00:35:03.900 --> 00:35:05.430 align:middle line:90%
---for a particular teaching.

00:35:05.430 --> 00:35:06.260 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:35:06.260 --> 00:35:08.250 align:middle line:90%
Yes, to help humanity.

00:35:08.250 --> 00:35:09.930 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:35:09.930 --> 00:35:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And some believe, and the
indigenous people in particular

00:35:14.750 --> 00:35:17.700 align:middle line:84%
believe, that if at some
point the white lions

00:35:17.700 --> 00:35:21.170 align:middle line:84%
leave the face of
the earth, the future

00:35:21.170 --> 00:35:22.980 align:middle line:90%
is very dark for all of us.

00:35:22.980 --> 00:35:27.570 align:middle line:84%
So people are working very
hard to have this not happen.

00:35:27.570 --> 00:35:29.040 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:35:29.040 --> 00:35:30.280 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:35:30.280 --> 00:35:34.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, what I'd like to do is
after all that-- so it's all

00:35:34.120 --> 00:35:37.360 align:middle line:84%
so powerful, so emotional--
is turn our conversation

00:35:37.360 --> 00:35:38.720 align:middle line:84%
to something equally
as emotional,

00:35:38.720 --> 00:35:42.170 align:middle line:84%
and that is our dear little
pets-- the domesticated ones

00:35:42.170 --> 00:35:43.540 align:middle line:84%
that are no longer
in the wild, that

00:35:43.540 --> 00:35:47.011 align:middle line:84%
live alongside us, whom you
have dealt with for a lifetime.

00:35:47.011 --> 00:35:47.980 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.
Yes.

00:35:47.980 --> 00:35:51.320 align:middle line:84%
And I would like to start
out by finding-- maybe we'll

00:35:51.320 --> 00:35:54.070 align:middle line:84%
start at the beginning with
talking about some more

00:35:54.070 --> 00:35:58.330 align:middle line:84%
challenging aspects of having
dealt with all of us bringing

00:35:58.330 --> 00:36:01.120 align:middle line:84%
our little broken
animals to you as a vet

00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:03.880 align:middle line:84%
when you can talk with them
and communicate in this way.

00:36:03.880 --> 00:36:04.770 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:36:04.770 --> 00:36:10.960 align:middle line:84%
I particularly love when
people bring in injured birds,

00:36:10.960 --> 00:36:12.690 align:middle line:90%
injured wildlife.

00:36:12.690 --> 00:36:14.470 align:middle line:90%
And then they apologize for it.

00:36:14.470 --> 00:36:16.050 align:middle line:84%
And I give them
my little tutorial

00:36:16.050 --> 00:36:17.330 align:middle line:90%
about please don't do that.

00:36:17.330 --> 00:36:18.480 align:middle line:90%
We need people like you.

00:36:18.480 --> 00:36:20.850 align:middle line:84%
You're really brave
and wonderful.

00:36:20.850 --> 00:36:25.010 align:middle line:84%
And oh gosh, there's
so many stories.

00:36:25.010 --> 00:36:32.179 align:middle line:84%
But the ones I find
the hardest are still

00:36:32.179 --> 00:36:37.630 align:middle line:84%
are people when they bring
their pets in for euthanasia.

00:36:37.630 --> 00:36:40.090 align:middle line:84%
Yes, that is a topic
I wanted to spend

00:36:40.090 --> 00:36:44.271 align:middle line:84%
some time on that is a very
difficult topic for everyone.

00:36:44.271 --> 00:36:44.970 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:36:44.970 --> 00:36:50.660 align:middle line:84%
And so many people have pets--
as I say, companion animals.

00:36:50.660 --> 00:36:53.020 align:middle line:84%
So many people
have dogs and cats.

00:36:53.020 --> 00:36:56.240 align:middle line:84%
And those dogs and
cats, you know,

00:36:56.240 --> 00:36:59.320 align:middle line:84%
dogs and cats used
to be outside.

00:36:59.320 --> 00:37:03.290 align:middle line:84%
Dogs used to be
out in dog houses.

00:37:03.290 --> 00:37:04.590 align:middle line:90%
Not anymore.

00:37:04.590 --> 00:37:06.715 align:middle line:84%
They're not only in our
homes, they're in our beds.

00:37:06.715 --> 00:37:07.470 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:37:07.470 --> 00:37:09.700 align:middle line:84%
You know, they're
not Fido anymore.

00:37:09.700 --> 00:37:12.870 align:middle line:84%
They're given names as
children would be given names.

00:37:12.870 --> 00:37:14.305 align:middle line:84%
-Yeah, like Eric.
-Eric.

00:37:14.305 --> 00:37:15.821 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS]
-Yes.

00:37:15.821 --> 00:37:17.470 align:middle line:84%
-Right.
-Patty, Susan, whatever.

00:37:17.470 --> 00:37:19.880 align:middle line:84%
REGINA MEREDITH:
Yeah, that is true.

00:37:19.880 --> 00:37:24.100 align:middle line:84%
So these are dearly
beloved family members.

00:37:24.100 --> 00:37:27.060 align:middle line:84%
And when their lives
come toward the end,

00:37:27.060 --> 00:37:32.290 align:middle line:84%
this is often as
difficult-- how to handle

00:37:32.290 --> 00:37:36.720 align:middle line:84%
these situations, as it is with
any other human family member.

00:37:36.720 --> 00:37:40.271 align:middle line:84%
And there's so much
pain involved in it.

00:37:40.271 --> 00:37:40.970 align:middle line:90%
There is.

00:37:40.970 --> 00:37:42.701 align:middle line:84%
And it's such a
confused-- I mean--

00:37:42.701 --> 00:37:43.400 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: It is.

00:37:43.400 --> 00:37:46.460 align:middle line:84%
---I've gone through the passing
of our dog Finbar recently,

00:37:46.460 --> 00:37:47.820 align:middle line:84%
which I'll share
that story with you.

00:37:47.820 --> 00:37:54.930 align:middle line:84%
But many years prior, I
dealt with my first real,

00:37:54.930 --> 00:37:57.090 align:middle line:84%
I mean, soul mate dog.
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:37:57.090 --> 00:37:58.740 align:middle line:90%
I've had many dogs I love.

00:37:58.740 --> 00:38:00.130 align:middle line:90%
I've had them my whole life.

00:38:00.130 --> 00:38:04.950 align:middle line:84%
But this one, named Sugar Bear,
who was a [INAUDIBLE] mix,

00:38:04.950 --> 00:38:06.495 align:middle line:90%
we were just bound together.

00:38:06.495 --> 00:38:11.390 align:middle line:84%
And through a circumstance
that occurred, she aged.

00:38:11.390 --> 00:38:13.340 align:middle line:84%
And through some
stress that happened

00:38:13.340 --> 00:38:16.340 align:middle line:84%
in my life, which transferred
to her, she developed cancer.

00:38:16.340 --> 00:38:19.430 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I did the
last-minute lifesaving

00:38:19.430 --> 00:38:20.790 align:middle line:90%
operation, had it done.

00:38:20.790 --> 00:38:22.340 align:middle line:84%
I just couldn't
bear to let her go.

00:38:22.340 --> 00:38:23.039 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Right.

00:38:23.039 --> 00:38:26.650 align:middle line:84%
And it only bought her an
extra couple weeks at most.

00:38:26.650 --> 00:38:30.980 align:middle line:84%
And the vet told me, now, if
you see her gums go white,

00:38:30.980 --> 00:38:33.590 align:middle line:84%
and she starts becoming weak,
there's nothing more we can do.

00:38:33.590 --> 00:38:34.911 align:middle line:84%
She's having internal
hemorrhaging.

00:38:34.911 --> 00:38:37.380 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: Right.
-So that day did come.

00:38:37.380 --> 00:38:40.190 align:middle line:84%
And they said, you might
want to bring her in, then,

00:38:40.190 --> 00:38:42.040 align:middle line:84%
and no have her go
through that suffering.

00:38:42.040 --> 00:38:45.020 align:middle line:84%
Well, I hadn't dealt with
anything like this before.

00:38:45.020 --> 00:38:45.720 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Right.

00:38:45.720 --> 00:38:47.890 align:middle line:90%
I did take her in.

00:38:47.890 --> 00:38:51.100 align:middle line:84%
But I stopped at the park
first, and let her out

00:38:51.100 --> 00:38:54.220 align:middle line:84%
of the car-- she could barely
even get out-- just to see

00:38:54.220 --> 00:38:55.610 align:middle line:84%
if she'd chase the
squirrels, which

00:38:55.610 --> 00:38:56.820 align:middle line:90%
was her favorite thing to do.

00:38:56.820 --> 00:39:00.560 align:middle line:84%
I thought if she won't chase
the squirrels, it's really over.

00:39:00.560 --> 00:39:02.651 align:middle line:84%
I was just looking for
intervention of some kind.

00:39:02.651 --> 00:39:03.350 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:39:03.350 --> 00:39:06.350 align:middle line:84%
And so when I took her
in, I couldn't bear it.

00:39:06.350 --> 00:39:08.210 align:middle line:84%
And they said, I
don't think you want

00:39:08.210 --> 00:39:09.335 align:middle line:90%
to be here when this happens.

00:39:09.335 --> 00:39:10.967 align:middle line:90%
And this was a long time ago.

00:39:10.967 --> 00:39:11.900 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Long time ago.

00:39:11.900 --> 00:39:12.800 align:middle line:90%
And they took her.

00:39:12.800 --> 00:39:14.390 align:middle line:84%
And she turned back
and looked at me.

00:39:14.390 --> 00:39:17.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's the most
haunting, horrible moment.

00:39:17.140 --> 00:39:19.000 align:middle line:84%
I have never gotten
over it in my lifetime.

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:20.030 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't with her.

00:39:20.030 --> 00:39:20.790 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:39:20.790 --> 00:39:21.760 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:39:21.760 --> 00:39:24.050 align:middle line:84%
-This is not uncommon.
-No.

00:39:24.050 --> 00:39:27.021 align:middle line:84%
And you still have
that vision of leaving.

00:39:27.021 --> 00:39:30.170 align:middle line:84%
Yes.
And this is our beloved Finbar.

00:39:30.170 --> 00:39:33.960 align:middle line:84%
Finbar just died
about five weeks ago.

00:39:33.960 --> 00:39:36.830 align:middle line:84%
He was an older fellow, but he
looked that beautiful right up

00:39:36.830 --> 00:39:39.310 align:middle line:90%
to the very, very end.

00:39:39.310 --> 00:39:41.160 align:middle line:84%
And this is one of
those situations

00:39:41.160 --> 00:39:43.280 align:middle line:84%
where after Sugar
Bear, I decided

00:39:43.280 --> 00:39:45.340 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to do that again.
-Yes.

00:39:45.340 --> 00:39:48.540 align:middle line:84%
And so we let him go through
kind of the normal process,

00:39:48.540 --> 00:39:50.170 align:middle line:90%
but we kept intervening.

00:39:50.170 --> 00:39:54.140 align:middle line:84%
Thousands of dollars
later, IVs, staying

00:39:54.140 --> 00:39:56.640 align:middle line:84%
at the vet's office
for days at a time,

00:39:56.640 --> 00:39:58.390 align:middle line:84%
did not really buy him time.
LINDA BENDER: Right.

00:39:58.390 --> 00:40:01.490 align:middle line:84%
He was trying to crawl out to
a little area under the deck,

00:40:01.490 --> 00:40:05.300 align:middle line:84%
and be in the dirt
by himself, and go.

00:40:05.300 --> 00:40:06.510 align:middle line:90%
But we didn't know.

00:40:06.510 --> 00:40:08.920 align:middle line:84%
That brings up all
these questions.

00:40:08.920 --> 00:40:10.420 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:40:10.420 --> 00:40:12.200 align:middle line:90%
When do you really listen?

00:40:12.200 --> 00:40:14.350 align:middle line:84%
When should we have
known that Finbar just--

00:40:14.350 --> 00:40:15.811 align:middle line:84%
we needed to leave him alone?
-Right.

00:40:15.811 --> 00:40:16.510 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:40:16.510 --> 00:40:20.990 align:middle line:84%
Well, unfortunately, there
is not a simple answer

00:40:20.990 --> 00:40:21.920 align:middle line:90%
to this question.

00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:27.670 align:middle line:84%
But once again, I come back
to a life of heart connection

00:40:27.670 --> 00:40:29.350 align:middle line:90%
to animals.

00:40:29.350 --> 00:40:32.910 align:middle line:84%
And I believe, and I've often
advised this to people who

00:40:32.910 --> 00:40:34.660 align:middle line:90%
say to me, when will I know?

00:40:34.660 --> 00:40:36.230 align:middle line:90%
When will I know?

00:40:36.230 --> 00:40:40.440 align:middle line:84%
And I often say to people-- I
look deeply into them so they

00:40:40.440 --> 00:40:43.120 align:middle line:90%
really hear from their hearts.

00:40:43.120 --> 00:40:49.870 align:middle line:84%
And I say, you will know if you
pay attention and you listen.

00:40:49.870 --> 00:40:53.420 align:middle line:84%
Or if you don't go into fear
and let that override you.

00:40:53.420 --> 00:40:56.780 align:middle line:84%
Listen to the heart
connection from your animal.

00:40:56.780 --> 00:40:58.340 align:middle line:90%
And there will be signs.

00:40:58.340 --> 00:41:01.556 align:middle line:84%
You know, there are
the usual signs.

00:41:01.556 --> 00:41:03.390 align:middle line:90%
You know, not eating as much.

00:41:03.390 --> 00:41:05.290 align:middle line:90%
They're the basic things.

00:41:05.290 --> 00:41:06.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, this was way
past all the signs.

00:41:06.590 --> 00:41:07.590 align:middle line:84%
Right.
He had those.

00:41:07.590 --> 00:41:09.030 align:middle line:84%
And he hadn't
been really eating.

00:41:09.030 --> 00:41:11.000 align:middle line:84%
We'd been feeding him
with a turkey baster,

00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:12.731 align:middle line:84%
little protein shakes
just to keep him alive.

00:41:12.731 --> 00:41:13.690 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: Right.
Right.

00:41:13.690 --> 00:41:15.660 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't-- I mean,
I look back and think,

00:41:15.660 --> 00:41:17.861 align:middle line:84%
what an undignified
thing to put him through.

00:41:17.861 --> 00:41:18.560 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:41:18.560 --> 00:41:21.680 align:middle line:84%
So we go through all
those medical signals.

00:41:21.680 --> 00:41:25.160 align:middle line:84%
And then there's still that
time when they may be lingering.

00:41:25.160 --> 00:41:28.730 align:middle line:84%
And I do believe that
animals, especially dogs

00:41:28.730 --> 00:41:31.180 align:middle line:84%
and that loving,
loving connection,

00:41:31.180 --> 00:41:34.890 align:middle line:84%
and that bond that is so
close with their owner,

00:41:34.890 --> 00:41:37.190 align:middle line:90%
they want so much to please.

00:41:37.190 --> 00:41:39.080 align:middle line:84%
And they want to stay--
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:41:39.080 --> 00:41:41.200 align:middle line:84%
---because they see
that you need them.

00:41:41.200 --> 00:41:43.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
confusing point, where

00:41:43.490 --> 00:41:45.170 align:middle line:90%
you keep trying to save them.

00:41:45.170 --> 00:41:48.260 align:middle line:84%
We keep trying to save
them, and they perhaps--

00:41:48.260 --> 00:41:53.160 align:middle line:84%
you know, they, in my
experience-- animals live

00:41:53.160 --> 00:41:57.750 align:middle line:84%
in a connection that is more
connected to the universal

00:41:57.750 --> 00:41:59.910 align:middle line:90%
connectedness than humans.

00:41:59.910 --> 00:42:00.810 align:middle line:90%
Yes, by far.

00:42:00.810 --> 00:42:03.980 align:middle line:84%
So I think they're
slightly more tuned in.

00:42:03.980 --> 00:42:05.420 align:middle line:90%
Animals experience fear.

00:42:05.420 --> 00:42:06.390 align:middle line:90%
Don't get me wrong.

00:42:06.390 --> 00:42:11.050 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think that they
are as afraid to let go.

00:42:11.050 --> 00:42:14.490 align:middle line:84%
And their main concern
is our well being.

00:42:14.490 --> 00:42:16.080 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:42:16.080 --> 00:42:19.710 align:middle line:84%
So we need to do our
part to help them along.

00:42:19.710 --> 00:42:21.750 align:middle line:84%
So in a situation
like this, which other

00:42:21.750 --> 00:42:23.449 align:middle line:84%
people have been through--
-A lot of them.

00:42:23.449 --> 00:42:24.320 align:middle line:90%
---he's an older dog.

00:42:24.320 --> 00:42:26.040 align:middle line:84%
He stopped eating.
-Yes.

00:42:26.040 --> 00:42:27.980 align:middle line:90%
He's seems to be in pain now.

00:42:27.980 --> 00:42:28.850 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.
Yes.

00:42:28.850 --> 00:42:29.884 align:middle line:84%
You know?
LINDA BENDER: Right.

00:42:29.884 --> 00:42:31.290 align:middle line:84%
What do you do?
You just [INAUDIBLE]?

00:42:31.290 --> 00:42:33.177 align:middle line:84%
You can cut back
on the heroics.

00:42:33.177 --> 00:42:33.910 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Yeah.

00:42:33.910 --> 00:42:35.210 align:middle line:90%
Cut back on the heroics.

00:42:35.210 --> 00:42:39.130 align:middle line:84%
And I have been-- for someone
who knows what I know,

00:42:39.130 --> 00:42:42.670 align:middle line:84%
I've been one to
push too far as well.

00:42:42.670 --> 00:42:46.150 align:middle line:84%
And then I'm reminded,
no, this is not about me.

00:42:46.150 --> 00:42:47.020 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Right.

00:42:47.020 --> 00:42:51.260 align:middle line:84%
It is about this being and
the quality of their life.

00:42:51.260 --> 00:42:55.140 align:middle line:84%
So we need to stop the
heroics to the extent we do.

00:42:55.140 --> 00:42:56.400 align:middle line:90%
And you're right.

00:42:56.400 --> 00:42:59.040 align:middle line:84%
When he hadn't eaten for
a week, then two weeks,

00:42:59.040 --> 00:43:01.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's a hint.
LINDA BENDER: Right.

00:43:01.030 --> 00:43:01.730 align:middle line:90%
He's done.

00:43:01.730 --> 00:43:02.710 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Right.

00:43:02.710 --> 00:43:04.850 align:middle line:84%
And there are two things that
I would like to bring up.

00:43:04.850 --> 00:43:09.120 align:middle line:84%
One is how we address the
situation of when we do

00:43:09.120 --> 00:43:12.591 align:middle line:84%
need to help that process
along with euthanasia.

00:43:12.591 --> 00:43:13.290 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:43:13.290 --> 00:43:23.720 align:middle line:84%
And also, you know, what we
can do to learn from animals

00:43:23.720 --> 00:43:25.430 align:middle line:84%
about the process
of dying-- you know,

00:43:25.430 --> 00:43:28.690 align:middle line:84%
they, unfortunately, don't
live as long as we do--

00:43:28.690 --> 00:43:32.281 align:middle line:84%
and what they're trying to teach
us about that dying process.

00:43:32.281 --> 00:43:33.990 align:middle line:84%
-For sure.
-Yeah.

00:43:33.990 --> 00:43:37.100 align:middle line:84%
And I learned-- I
could share a story--

00:43:37.100 --> 00:43:38.600 align:middle line:84%
REGINA MEREDITH: Please
do, because you had--

00:43:38.600 --> 00:43:40.540 align:middle line:84%
---of my dog Pepper.
-Pepper.

00:43:40.540 --> 00:43:42.421 align:middle line:84%
And Pepper's only been
gone about six months.

00:43:42.421 --> 00:43:43.120 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:43:43.120 --> 00:43:46.400 align:middle line:84%
And Pepper was one of my
dearest, dearest friends,

00:43:46.400 --> 00:43:47.190 align:middle line:90%
and still is.

00:43:47.190 --> 00:43:49.560 align:middle line:84%
We have a picture of
you and Pepper together.

00:43:49.560 --> 00:43:50.430 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:43:50.430 --> 00:43:57.890 align:middle line:84%
But Pepper was-- again, he
found me many, many years ago.

00:43:57.890 --> 00:44:02.420 align:middle line:84%
But he had a history
of autoimmune problems.

00:44:02.420 --> 00:44:04.630 align:middle line:84%
So I worked with
that over the years.

00:44:04.630 --> 00:44:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And it's a question of what I
can fix and what I can't fix,

00:44:09.090 --> 00:44:12.130 align:middle line:84%
using all different
types of methods,

00:44:12.130 --> 00:44:16.630 align:middle line:84%
traditional and alternative,
diet, all those things,

00:44:16.630 --> 00:44:18.670 align:middle line:90%
to keep your animal healthy.

00:44:18.670 --> 00:44:25.010 align:middle line:84%
And so Pepper, as he advanced in
years, had a series of issues.

00:44:25.010 --> 00:44:31.010 align:middle line:84%
And in the last year of his
life, I got up one morning.

00:44:31.010 --> 00:44:36.000 align:middle line:84%
And instead of him greeting
me at the food dish,

00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:38.420 align:middle line:84%
he was completely
flat on his side.

00:44:38.420 --> 00:44:41.050 align:middle line:84%
I thought, oh my god,
he wasn't moving.

00:44:41.050 --> 00:44:41.980 align:middle line:90%
I thought he was dead.

00:44:41.980 --> 00:44:44.630 align:middle line:90%
I ran over, felt this heart.

00:44:44.630 --> 00:44:47.130 align:middle line:90%
He was still barely breathing.

00:44:47.130 --> 00:44:49.660 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I don't
know what's going on.

00:44:49.660 --> 00:44:51.360 align:middle line:90%
This is a critical situation.

00:44:51.360 --> 00:44:52.830 align:middle line:90%
Should I just leave him?

00:44:52.830 --> 00:44:57.050 align:middle line:84%
Should I grab him, throw him in
the car, get him to the clinic

00:44:57.050 --> 00:44:58.660 align:middle line:90%
quickly?

00:44:58.660 --> 00:45:02.570 align:middle line:84%
I chose-- in my pajamas, lifted
him up, put him in my car,

00:45:02.570 --> 00:45:03.930 align:middle line:90%
got him to the clinic quickly.

00:45:03.930 --> 00:45:07.120 align:middle line:84%
And in that case, it was
the wise thing to do.

00:45:07.120 --> 00:45:08.660 align:middle line:90%
I did go for it.

00:45:08.660 --> 00:45:09.595 align:middle line:90%
I used my intuition.

00:45:09.595 --> 00:45:13.640 align:middle line:84%
It turned out he had a tumor in
his spleen that had ruptured,

00:45:13.640 --> 00:45:15.060 align:middle line:90%
so he was bleeding out.

00:45:15.060 --> 00:45:16.520 align:middle line:90%
We quickly got him in the OR.

00:45:16.520 --> 00:45:18.160 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I didn't
do any of this.

00:45:18.160 --> 00:45:19.480 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:45:19.480 --> 00:45:21.200 align:middle line:84%
Your hands might
have been unsteady.

00:45:21.200 --> 00:45:26.250 align:middle line:84%
But a dear friend did bring
him back, and he was fine.

00:45:26.250 --> 00:45:27.690 align:middle line:90%
He was good as new.

00:45:27.690 --> 00:45:30.570 align:middle line:84%
He went through a series
of other critical issues.

00:45:30.570 --> 00:45:34.110 align:middle line:90%
So again, when do we know?

00:45:34.110 --> 00:45:40.240 align:middle line:84%
But in the end, Pepper went
downhill fairly quickly.

00:45:40.240 --> 00:45:42.810 align:middle line:90%
I ran a few diagnostics on him.

00:45:42.810 --> 00:45:44.960 align:middle line:84%
We couldn't figure
out what was wrong.

00:45:44.960 --> 00:45:46.040 align:middle line:90%
I then looked at Pepper.

00:45:46.040 --> 00:45:47.800 align:middle line:90%
Pepper looked at me.

00:45:47.800 --> 00:45:52.956 align:middle line:84%
I knew I could no longer keep
this body going, nor could he.

00:45:52.956 --> 00:45:58.110 align:middle line:84%
He indicated
through me listening

00:45:58.110 --> 00:46:02.950 align:middle line:90%
that his body was wearing out.

00:46:02.950 --> 00:46:06.780 align:middle line:84%
The important thing I did
with him was completely

00:46:06.780 --> 00:46:10.570 align:middle line:84%
go out of a different
mode of thinking into how

00:46:10.570 --> 00:46:11.780 align:middle line:90%
can I make you comfortable.

00:46:11.780 --> 00:46:12.800 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:46:12.800 --> 00:46:13.910 align:middle line:90%
I stayed with him.

00:46:13.910 --> 00:46:15.070 align:middle line:90%
We hugged.

00:46:15.070 --> 00:46:17.470 align:middle line:84%
He used to love
to tuck his head.

00:46:17.470 --> 00:46:19.640 align:middle line:84%
We just clicked into
that mode of how

00:46:19.640 --> 00:46:21.780 align:middle line:90%
can we make the end better.

00:46:21.780 --> 00:46:23.890 align:middle line:90%
And he did die in my arms.

00:46:23.890 --> 00:46:26.760 align:middle line:84%
And now, like you
and your last case,

00:46:26.760 --> 00:46:28.930 align:middle line:84%
when I look back at
Pepper, and I remember,

00:46:28.930 --> 00:46:31.140 align:middle line:90%
I do think of that end moment.

00:46:31.140 --> 00:46:33.550 align:middle line:84%
But I have tremendous
consolation knowing

00:46:33.550 --> 00:46:34.620 align:middle line:90%
that I was there with him.

00:46:34.620 --> 00:46:36.260 align:middle line:84%
Yes, the end moments
are hard when you

00:46:36.260 --> 00:46:37.450 align:middle line:90%
allow it to happen naturally.

00:46:37.450 --> 00:46:40.305 align:middle line:84%
Euthanasia is
less-- emotionally,

00:46:40.305 --> 00:46:44.640 align:middle line:84%
a very traumatic decision, but
it is less difficult to watch

00:46:44.640 --> 00:46:47.446 align:middle line:84%
than it is when you see Pepper,
or in this case, Finbar, die

00:46:47.446 --> 00:46:49.180 align:middle line:84%
naturally.
-Yes.

00:46:49.180 --> 00:46:50.140 align:middle line:90%
But as you say--

00:46:50.140 --> 00:46:53.890 align:middle line:84%
So many people, loving
their animals so much,

00:46:53.890 --> 00:46:56.880 align:middle line:84%
find it too difficult
to go to the vet

00:46:56.880 --> 00:46:59.660 align:middle line:84%
when they know
intervention is needed.

00:46:59.660 --> 00:47:02.820 align:middle line:84%
And what I would
like people to know

00:47:02.820 --> 00:47:06.030 align:middle line:84%
is that animal needs
you at that moment

00:47:06.030 --> 00:47:09.050 align:middle line:84%
more than any other
time in its life,

00:47:09.050 --> 00:47:10.972 align:middle line:90%
and that it isn't about you.

00:47:10.972 --> 00:47:15.200 align:middle line:84%
You need to rally to
be with your animal

00:47:15.200 --> 00:47:19.640 align:middle line:84%
during that last moment at the
clinic, when your animal does

00:47:19.640 --> 00:47:21.070 align:middle line:90%
require euthanasia.

00:47:21.070 --> 00:47:22.390 align:middle line:90%
Be there, holding your pet.

00:47:22.390 --> 00:47:25.360 align:middle line:84%
And if you cannot,
there are others

00:47:25.360 --> 00:47:27.160 align:middle line:90%
who might be able to step in.

00:47:27.160 --> 00:47:30.890 align:middle line:84%
Before we get to that part,
which I think is really--

00:47:30.890 --> 00:47:33.930 align:middle line:84%
you have another amazing
story about that.

00:47:33.930 --> 00:47:36.530 align:middle line:84%
Is it a matter of when
they're in too much pain?

00:47:36.530 --> 00:47:38.450 align:middle line:84%
What is the determining
factor of when

00:47:38.450 --> 00:47:41.610 align:middle line:84%
you let it take its own course
versus when intervention

00:47:41.610 --> 00:47:43.640 align:middle line:90%
might be a good thing?

00:47:43.640 --> 00:47:45.355 align:middle line:84%
Well, as you just
mentioned, pain.

00:47:45.355 --> 00:47:47.059 align:middle line:84%
REGINA MEREDITH: Pain, yeah.
Excruciating pain.

00:47:47.059 --> 00:47:47.780 align:middle line:90%
Pain is huge.

00:47:47.780 --> 00:47:50.523 align:middle line:84%
And think of your
human loved ones.

00:47:50.523 --> 00:47:51.256 align:middle line:90%
REGINA MEREDITH: Yeah.

00:47:51.256 --> 00:47:52.590 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:47:52.590 --> 00:47:55.740 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to see
our loved ones in pain.

00:47:55.740 --> 00:47:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And then when you have
communicated with animals that

00:47:58.470 --> 00:48:00.800 align:middle line:84%
are in extreme pain,
and that have been

00:48:00.800 --> 00:48:02.990 align:middle line:84%
brought in for
euthanasia, are they,

00:48:02.990 --> 00:48:05.410 align:middle line:90%
like-- are they open to this?

00:48:05.410 --> 00:48:06.700 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely.
REGINA MEREDITH: They are.

00:48:06.700 --> 00:48:08.120 align:middle line:84%
OK.
-I do believe they are.

00:48:08.120 --> 00:48:10.740 align:middle line:90%
I do believe they are.

00:48:10.740 --> 00:48:12.419 align:middle line:84%
Yes.
-OK.

00:48:12.419 --> 00:48:14.050 align:middle line:84%
You know, all beings
want to stay alive.

00:48:14.050 --> 00:48:16.470 align:middle line:90%
They want to thrive.

00:48:16.470 --> 00:48:18.670 align:middle line:90%
Animals in pain are quite ready.

00:48:18.670 --> 00:48:19.830 align:middle line:90%
As I believe are humans.

00:48:19.830 --> 00:48:20.530 align:middle line:90%
Are humans.

00:48:20.530 --> 00:48:22.079 align:middle line:84%
Humans are too.
LINDA BENDER: Yeah.

00:48:22.079 --> 00:48:24.125 align:middle line:84%
Now, you have a story
about a woman named Jean.

00:48:24.125 --> 00:48:27.180 align:middle line:84%
And this gets us back
to the euthanasia.

00:48:27.180 --> 00:48:29.660 align:middle line:84%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.
Right.

00:48:29.660 --> 00:48:31.950 align:middle line:84%
Again, I was giving
a talk one day.

00:48:31.950 --> 00:48:35.110 align:middle line:84%
And a woman came
up to me afterward.

00:48:35.110 --> 00:48:37.880 align:middle line:90%
And she was quite emotional.

00:48:37.880 --> 00:48:40.070 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I don't know
how you do what you do.

00:48:40.070 --> 00:48:41.320 align:middle line:90%
How do you do what you do?

00:48:41.320 --> 00:48:42.340 align:middle line:90%
I love animals.

00:48:42.340 --> 00:48:43.070 align:middle line:90%
I want to help.

00:48:43.070 --> 00:48:44.930 align:middle line:90%
It hurts too much.

00:48:44.930 --> 00:48:46.410 align:middle line:90%
I just lost my dog.

00:48:46.410 --> 00:48:52.840 align:middle line:84%
I could barely stand being
there during the euthanasia.

00:48:52.840 --> 00:48:54.590 align:middle line:84%
She said, I don't
know what I can do.

00:48:54.590 --> 00:48:56.470 align:middle line:90%
I just am breaking down.

00:48:56.470 --> 00:48:58.260 align:middle line:90%
So I told her a wonderful story.

00:48:58.260 --> 00:49:01.000 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, first of
all, why I do what I do.

00:49:01.000 --> 00:49:03.390 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you a quick story.

00:49:03.390 --> 00:49:08.340 align:middle line:84%
And I really wanted to cheer her
up, because I said, all right.

00:49:08.340 --> 00:49:11.120 align:middle line:84%
For the past five years,
I teach young people.

00:49:11.120 --> 00:49:12.530 align:middle line:90%
I teach high school students.

00:49:12.530 --> 00:49:15.240 align:middle line:84%
And I teach them
about the environment,

00:49:15.240 --> 00:49:17.220 align:middle line:90%
about all sorts of things.

00:49:17.220 --> 00:49:21.010 align:middle line:84%
And I work my magic into
animals and the environment.

00:49:21.010 --> 00:49:25.970 align:middle line:84%
So I was heading to a class
one morning, leaving my home,

00:49:25.970 --> 00:49:27.700 align:middle line:84%
and I had to stop
by the Apple Store

00:49:27.700 --> 00:49:30.500 align:middle line:84%
and pick up some equipment
to use for my talk,

00:49:30.500 --> 00:49:32.450 align:middle line:90%
so I was in a bit of a hurry.

00:49:32.450 --> 00:49:34.620 align:middle line:84%
Went down to the end of
my street, turned right.

00:49:34.620 --> 00:49:37.760 align:middle line:84%
And as I entered a
slightly bigger street,

00:49:37.760 --> 00:49:42.120 align:middle line:84%
I saw this lump of feathers
on the side of the road,

00:49:42.120 --> 00:49:45.780 align:middle line:84%
almost getting a little
too close to the road.

00:49:45.780 --> 00:49:49.990 align:middle line:84%
So of course, as I
usually do, or always do,

00:49:49.990 --> 00:49:53.140 align:middle line:84%
I stopped my car in
the middle of the road,

00:49:53.140 --> 00:49:57.050 align:middle line:84%
opened the door wide to
try to block the traffic.

00:49:57.050 --> 00:50:00.010 align:middle line:84%
And I dashed across
the road, and there,

00:50:00.010 --> 00:50:05.380 align:middle line:84%
in a hump on the road, was
this enormous turkey vulture.

00:50:05.380 --> 00:50:07.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, how often do we
see turkey vultures?

00:50:07.530 --> 00:50:10.430 align:middle line:84%
They're a large
lump of feathers.

00:50:10.430 --> 00:50:12.930 align:middle line:90%
Obviously in distress.

00:50:12.930 --> 00:50:17.640 align:middle line:84%
Was about to get onto the road,
and unfortunately, be hit.

00:50:17.640 --> 00:50:18.760 align:middle line:90%
So I dashed over.

00:50:18.760 --> 00:50:20.050 align:middle line:90%
Thought, what am I going to do?

00:50:20.050 --> 00:50:23.320 align:middle line:84%
Reached down, grabbed
this enormous turkey

00:50:23.320 --> 00:50:24.270 align:middle line:90%
vulture in my arms.

00:50:24.270 --> 00:50:25.220 align:middle line:90%
It was a female.

00:50:25.220 --> 00:50:26.930 align:middle line:90%
You could tell by the markings.

00:50:26.930 --> 00:50:28.860 align:middle line:90%
And she let me pick her up.

00:50:28.860 --> 00:50:30.259 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, OK.
Great.

00:50:30.259 --> 00:50:31.300 align:middle line:90%
What are we going to do now?

00:50:31.300 --> 00:50:35.140 align:middle line:84%
So I marched over to
my car, managed to open

00:50:35.140 --> 00:50:39.030 align:middle line:90%
the car door with my foot.

00:50:39.030 --> 00:50:43.155 align:middle line:84%
Turkey vulture and I got
in my Prius, shut the door,

00:50:43.155 --> 00:50:44.550 align:middle line:84%
thought, what are
we going to do?

00:50:44.550 --> 00:50:46.590 align:middle line:90%
I put her in the passenger seat.

00:50:46.590 --> 00:50:48.390 align:middle line:84%
We dashed over to
the Apple Store.

00:50:48.390 --> 00:50:50.390 align:middle line:90%
I parked and I said, don't move.

00:50:50.390 --> 00:50:51.160 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:51.160 --> 00:50:53.510 align:middle line:90%
Like she could fly away, right?

00:50:53.510 --> 00:50:54.930 align:middle line:90%
She was listening.

00:50:54.930 --> 00:50:58.970 align:middle line:84%
I went into the Apple Store,
got my buddies to help me.

00:50:58.970 --> 00:51:01.460 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I gotta go.
I've gotta go.

00:51:01.460 --> 00:51:04.570 align:middle line:84%
I've got this enormous
bird in my car, tada tada.

00:51:04.570 --> 00:51:05.930 align:middle line:90%
So he said, I'll help you out.

00:51:05.930 --> 00:51:07.990 align:middle line:84%
We dashed out to
the parking lot.

00:51:07.990 --> 00:51:11.160 align:middle line:84%
I turned around, and not only
was my one Apple employee

00:51:11.160 --> 00:51:13.680 align:middle line:84%
friend there, but there was
a string of about 20 others

00:51:13.680 --> 00:51:15.700 align:middle line:90%
all wanting to see.

00:51:15.700 --> 00:51:16.530 align:middle line:90%
Got in the car.

00:51:16.530 --> 00:51:19.200 align:middle line:90%
There was my turkey vulture.

00:51:19.200 --> 00:51:22.510 align:middle line:84%
What I did was drive
her over to a friend's

00:51:22.510 --> 00:51:25.590 align:middle line:90%
rescue and rehab facility.

00:51:25.590 --> 00:51:27.030 align:middle line:90%
She was there, luckily.

00:51:27.030 --> 00:51:29.660 align:middle line:84%
We put the vulture in
the cage, because there

00:51:29.660 --> 00:51:32.410 align:middle line:84%
was no immediate
sign of acute trauma.

00:51:32.410 --> 00:51:34.490 align:middle line:90%
I said, let's leave her here.

00:51:34.490 --> 00:51:37.140 align:middle line:90%
I'll be back later tonight.

00:51:37.140 --> 00:51:38.450 align:middle line:90%
So I went up on my day.

00:51:38.450 --> 00:51:41.460 align:middle line:84%
She called me and
said, I think we're OK.

00:51:41.460 --> 00:51:42.160 align:middle line:90%
OK, I said.

00:51:42.160 --> 00:51:43.860 align:middle line:90%
I can't get over till 9 o'clock.

00:51:43.860 --> 00:51:45.390 align:middle line:84%
I said, can we wait
till the morning?

00:51:45.390 --> 00:51:47.070 align:middle line:90%
She said, I think we can.

00:51:47.070 --> 00:51:50.390 align:middle line:84%
First thing the next morning,
she rang me and said, Linda,

00:51:50.390 --> 00:51:52.660 align:middle line:84%
get over here as
fast as you can.

00:51:52.660 --> 00:51:55.160 align:middle line:84%
We have got to let this bird
go because if not, she's

00:51:55.160 --> 00:51:56.735 align:middle line:90%
going to break my cage.

00:51:56.735 --> 00:51:58.720 align:middle line:90%
I dashed over there.

00:51:58.720 --> 00:52:00.970 align:middle line:90%
There she was.

00:52:00.970 --> 00:52:02.810 align:middle line:90%
Whatever was wrong was--

00:52:02.810 --> 00:52:03.891 align:middle line:84%
Right.
---no longer wrong.

00:52:03.891 --> 00:52:06.010 align:middle line:84%
-Was right.
-Was right.

00:52:06.010 --> 00:52:08.160 align:middle line:90%
And she was fierce.

00:52:08.160 --> 00:52:13.050 align:middle line:84%
So I went over and I opened
this enormous wire door.

00:52:13.050 --> 00:52:16.720 align:middle line:84%
And she stepped
out so gracefully.

00:52:16.720 --> 00:52:20.875 align:middle line:84%
And she righted her body
and looked at me straight

00:52:20.875 --> 00:52:24.300 align:middle line:90%
in the eyes, and a thank you.

00:52:24.300 --> 00:52:28.590 align:middle line:84%
And then she turned and
flew up into the trees.

00:52:28.590 --> 00:52:31.567 align:middle line:84%
Now, I don't know if you've ever
seen a turkey vulture wingspan.

00:52:31.567 --> 00:52:32.700 align:middle line:84%
REGINA MEREDITH:
In California, we

00:52:32.700 --> 00:52:34.260 align:middle line:90%
have them all around our house.

00:52:34.260 --> 00:52:35.240 align:middle line:90%
I see them all the time.

00:52:35.240 --> 00:52:37.090 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: 7 foot huge.

00:52:37.090 --> 00:52:38.660 align:middle line:84%
It took my breath away--
-Yes.

00:52:38.660 --> 00:52:42.700 align:middle line:84%
---as I watched her
fly up into the trees,

00:52:42.700 --> 00:52:44.720 align:middle line:90%
having a second chance at life.

00:52:44.720 --> 00:52:46.010 align:middle line:90%
That's why I do what I do.

00:52:46.010 --> 00:52:47.476 align:middle line:84%
Second chance at life.
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:52:47.476 --> 00:52:48.411 align:middle line:90%
Now Jean--

00:52:48.411 --> 00:52:49.410 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: So I told Jean--

00:52:49.410 --> 00:52:50.280 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:52:50.280 --> 00:52:52.280 align:middle line:90%
Jean listened to the story.

00:52:52.280 --> 00:52:54.981 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you know, there
are a lot of things you can do,

00:52:54.981 --> 00:52:57.240 align:middle line:84%
Jean.
I know you love dogs.

00:52:57.240 --> 00:53:00.590 align:middle line:84%
I know you want to honor
the dog you just lost.

00:53:00.590 --> 00:53:02.880 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you call
a few vet clinics,

00:53:02.880 --> 00:53:05.360 align:middle line:84%
see what you can
do to volunteer.

00:53:05.360 --> 00:53:08.280 align:middle line:84%
About two months later, I
got a phone call from Jean.

00:53:08.280 --> 00:53:09.430 align:middle line:90%
She was ecstatic.

00:53:09.430 --> 00:53:11.760 align:middle line:84%
She said, Linda, I
couldn't wait to tell you.

00:53:11.760 --> 00:53:16.010 align:middle line:84%
I am now on call volunteering
when people cannot

00:53:16.010 --> 00:53:19.390 align:middle line:84%
face holding their
animals when they're about

00:53:19.390 --> 00:53:20.840 align:middle line:84%
to be put to sleep.
I go.

00:53:20.840 --> 00:53:22.800 align:middle line:90%
I comfort that animal.

00:53:22.800 --> 00:53:24.160 align:middle line:90%
That is just so beautiful.

00:53:24.160 --> 00:53:24.950 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:53:24.950 --> 00:53:29.530 align:middle line:84%
And that is her mission,
and that's her [INAUDIBLE].

00:53:29.530 --> 00:53:30.610 align:middle line:90%
And any of us can do that?

00:53:30.610 --> 00:53:31.580 align:middle line:90%
Any of us can do that.

00:53:31.580 --> 00:53:34.070 align:middle line:84%
To hold that energy
for a little animal

00:53:34.070 --> 00:53:35.511 align:middle line:84%
so they don't go
out on their own.

00:53:35.511 --> 00:53:37.890 align:middle line:84%
-Right.
-Oh, I just love that.

00:53:37.890 --> 00:53:40.381 align:middle line:84%
And every time she does
it, it honors her dog.

00:53:40.381 --> 00:53:41.845 align:middle line:84%
-Yes.
-Yeah.

00:53:41.845 --> 00:53:43.240 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:53:43.240 --> 00:53:45.200 align:middle line:84%
I was just thinking
of something

00:53:45.200 --> 00:53:46.820 align:middle line:84%
when you were talking
about that turkey

00:53:46.820 --> 00:53:48.760 align:middle line:90%
vulture part of the story.

00:53:48.760 --> 00:53:50.860 align:middle line:84%
And one day, I was
contemplating something.

00:53:50.860 --> 00:53:52.760 align:middle line:84%
It was a deeper
question, and I was

00:53:52.760 --> 00:53:55.180 align:middle line:84%
really looking for an
answer and didn't have it.

00:53:55.180 --> 00:53:58.280 align:middle line:84%
I was looking for a sign about
something, whether to take

00:53:58.280 --> 00:53:59.250 align:middle line:90%
action on something.

00:53:59.250 --> 00:53:59.950 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:53:59.950 --> 00:54:02.760 align:middle line:10%
And as I was driving
down our lane,

00:54:02.760 --> 00:54:06.570 align:middle line:10%
this turkey vulture came
out and flew-- I mean,

00:54:06.570 --> 00:54:08.175 align:middle line:10%
it felt like it was 3
feet from the window.

00:54:08.175 --> 00:54:09.250 align:middle line:90%
It might have been 6 feet.

00:54:09.250 --> 00:54:10.410 align:middle line:90%
It was very close.

00:54:10.410 --> 00:54:11.220 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:54:11.220 --> 00:54:13.990 align:middle line:84%
And he had picked up a
snake, which was dangling

00:54:13.990 --> 00:54:17.700 align:middle line:84%
in his mouth, and flew right
in front of my windshield

00:54:17.700 --> 00:54:18.610 align:middle line:90%
with this snake.

00:54:18.610 --> 00:54:19.450 align:middle line:90%
Oh my.

00:54:19.450 --> 00:54:21.050 align:middle line:84%
And because of the
nature of the question,

00:54:21.050 --> 00:54:22.930 align:middle line:90%
I knew exactly what that meant.

00:54:22.930 --> 00:54:26.700 align:middle line:84%
And so the thing-- I mean, that
was just an amazing experience.

00:54:26.700 --> 00:54:28.581 align:middle line:84%
But that brings us to
the psychic part of it.

00:54:28.581 --> 00:54:29.280 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:54:29.280 --> 00:54:30.800 align:middle line:84%
We only have a
few minutes left.

00:54:30.800 --> 00:54:31.499 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:54:31.499 --> 00:54:33.550 align:middle line:84%
Now, some of us have learned
how to develop connections

00:54:33.550 --> 00:54:36.910 align:middle line:84%
with spirit guides, whatever
you want to call it,

00:54:36.910 --> 00:54:38.941 align:middle line:84%
all these different
forces around us.

00:54:38.941 --> 00:54:39.640 align:middle line:90%
LINDA BENDER: Yes.

00:54:39.640 --> 00:54:41.470 align:middle line:84%
And we learned how
to open and listen.

00:54:41.470 --> 00:54:43.990 align:middle line:84%
Is it basically the
same process if we

00:54:43.990 --> 00:54:45.200 align:middle line:90%
want to connect with our pets?

00:54:45.200 --> 00:54:47.140 align:middle line:90%
Same intention, same process?

00:54:47.140 --> 00:54:48.200 align:middle line:90%
It totally is.

00:54:48.200 --> 00:54:50.860 align:middle line:10%
And I always say to people,
I've been a meditator

00:54:50.860 --> 00:54:52.760 align:middle line:10%
for many, many, many years.
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:54:52.760 --> 00:54:55.270 align:middle line:10%
If there's one thing you want
to do to make your life better,

00:54:55.270 --> 00:55:00.990 align:middle line:10%
to tune into not only yourself,
but all life around you,

00:55:00.990 --> 00:55:02.570 align:middle line:10%
it's meditation.
REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:55:02.570 --> 00:55:06.820 align:middle line:84%
And with animals, whether they
be wild animals or companion

00:55:06.820 --> 00:55:10.860 align:middle line:84%
animals, it's so much about
listening and opening,

00:55:10.860 --> 00:55:13.680 align:middle line:84%
and again, seeing
that invitation

00:55:13.680 --> 00:55:17.280 align:middle line:84%
that is always there for those
who are willing to respond.

00:55:17.280 --> 00:55:19.070 align:middle line:84%
The other thing I
find with animals

00:55:19.070 --> 00:55:21.360 align:middle line:90%
and messages, two things.

00:55:21.360 --> 00:55:25.620 align:middle line:84%
One is people cling
to an animal totem.

00:55:25.620 --> 00:55:28.220 align:middle line:84%
I believe that all
animals are totems.

00:55:28.220 --> 00:55:30.610 align:middle line:84%
And so don't
disregard if an animal

00:55:30.610 --> 00:55:35.180 align:middle line:84%
that you don't know
familiarly as a totem

00:55:35.180 --> 00:55:37.220 align:middle line:90%
comes to you in some way.

00:55:37.220 --> 00:55:38.030 align:middle line:90%
Listen.

00:55:38.030 --> 00:55:40.660 align:middle line:84%
Always be willing
to listen to what

00:55:40.660 --> 00:55:43.860 align:middle line:90%
any animal is bringing to us.

00:55:43.860 --> 00:55:45.760 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that
it isn't necessarily

00:55:45.760 --> 00:55:47.890 align:middle line:84%
the animal specifically
who was doing that.

00:55:47.890 --> 00:55:51.660 align:middle line:84%
I believe it is the
workings of the universe--

00:55:51.660 --> 00:55:56.280 align:middle line:84%
even other humans on the
other side using animals.

00:55:56.280 --> 00:55:59.720 align:middle line:84%
An animal may be doing
something, crossing your path,

00:55:59.720 --> 00:56:04.430 align:middle line:84%
not even necessarily
aware, but its presence is

00:56:04.430 --> 00:56:07.470 align:middle line:84%
guided there by higher forces.
-Yes.

00:56:07.470 --> 00:56:08.680 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't agree more.

00:56:08.680 --> 00:56:10.280 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for that.
-Yes.

00:56:10.280 --> 00:56:12.280 align:middle line:84%
